@startuml activity-link-hints
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because the hint flow is a DECISION pipeline (collect to label to type to match?)
'' with three outcomes (follow / cancel / keep filtering); a coloured PlantUML activity shows the path
'' end-to-end, with the per-keystroke filtering loop called out in the note.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Vimium link hints — f then a label then follow\n[:ui :hints] = active? + targets + typed

skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #EAF6FF
  BorderColor #4C66AE
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF6D6
  DiamondBorderColor IPC_BORDER
  FontColor #1A1A1A
}

start
:press f (resolver, Vim normal) then dispatch hint/start; <<RENDERER_TINT>>
:hints/collect — every visible link in the content pane,\nclassify (file / http / dir / anchor) + viewport position; <<KEYMAP_TINT>>
:hints/with-labels — uniform-length unique labels\nfrom a home-row alphabet (SADFJKLEWCMPGH); <<KEYMAP_TINT>>
:ui-hints state becomes active; overlay drawn; <<APPDB_TINT>>
:overlay draws a label badge over each link; <<RENDERER_TINT>>
:type a label character; typed grows;\nmatches = targets whose label starts-with typed; <<APPDB_TINT>>
if (how many labels still match?) then (exactly 1)
  :follow — file to doc/open · http to web view\n· dir to open-path · anchor to scroll-into-view; <<IPC_TINT>>
else (zero, or Esc)
  :clear the hints (cancel); <<APPDB_TINT>>
endif
stop

note right #FFF6D6
  Per-keystroke loop: the type step repeats while two or more labels match — non-matching badges hide and
  filtering continues; Backspace pops a char; the decision above resolves the typing. A capture-phase window
  key listener owns the keyboard ONLY while hints are active (pre-empting the global resolver), so f itself
  still reaches the resolver to START hinting. PDF pages are excluded (Chromium's plugin viewer cannot be
  script-injected); HTTP pages run their own self-contained f-hint mode injected by web-preload.js.
end note

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  |<#2D9574>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| renderer UI (resolver, overlay) |
  |<#BC6EC5>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| hints engine (collect + labels) |
  |<#7590DB>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| app-db [:ui :hints] |
  |<#B1951D>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| follow the link (navigation fx) |
endlegend
@enduml
